    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n## Description\nWhen using Neovim 0.12 inside a tmux split with `status-position top` set in tmux config, \nan extra blank line appears at the top of every Neovim window and a grey line appears at \nthe bottom below the statusline. This does not occur when:\n- Running Neovim fullscreen (no tmux split)\n- Running with tmux status bar disabled (`tmux set status off`)\n- Using tmux with `status-position bottom`\n\n## Actual Behavior\nExtra blank line at top of window, grey line at bottom below statusline\n\n## Environment\n- Neovim 0.12.2\n- tmux 3.6b\n- Terminal: Alacritty\n- OS: Arch Linux (Omarchy)\n- LazyVim\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n## Steps to Reproduce\n1. Add `set -g status-position top` to ~/.tmux.conf\n2. Reload tmux config\n3. Open a tmux split pane\n4. Run `nvim --clean` in the split\n5. Observe empty line at top and grey line at bottom of the window\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNeovim renders correctly with no extra blank lines.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.2\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nvim 9.2\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux / Omarchy 3.8.2 \n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.17.0 (94e7c887)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
