            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> an extra blank line appears at the top of every Neovim window and a grey line appears at\nthe bottom below the statusline. This does not occur when:\n\n1. I see no blank line at the top. Please correct me\n2. a \"blank line\" on the bottom is normal. Lets assume your font size is 12px, your terminal window has a height of 200px, so it can display 16 full lines and there are 8px left that it show. What you see as \"blank line\" are blank pixels of the terminal (not vim/neovim) (**simplified math, ignoring line spacing**)\n4. If `set cmdheight=1`, vim/neovim shows allways the cmdline, which is in most cases empty. you can set it to =0 to verify 2)",
            "created_at": "2026-05-29T11:30:50Z",
